# More than 256 values live simultaneously — every `t` below is bound
# before any of them is read, so all 300 are live at the last binding.
#
# This is the case the `u8` register operand could not encode. It was never
# a frame-size limit: `bytecode_function::register_count` was always a
# `uint16_t` and the VM sized frames straight from it, so the ceiling was
# purely the operand encoding. Register allocation alone cannot help here —
# these values genuinely overlap, so there is nothing to recycle.
#
# The `# expect:` value is mandatory rather than relying on the two backends
# agreeing (CLAUDE.md): only the bytecode tier has a register file, so
# agreement cannot detect a register-addressing bug at all.
# expect: 1504

module codegen_stress.wide_simultaneous_liveness

def main() -> int32:
